snippet.textDisplay:
Once again listened this today as i have done numerous times, and for the people who don't understand punjabi, you can use the "CC " button for Subtitles, which equally depict the central idea of the song.

 Gurdas Maan (the legend of punjab) must have written this song decades back, but i think like old is gold, this song and lyrics will resonate in the decades to come. using simple language he gives a strong and touching message in this composition too, as he always does with his pen and soulful voice. As always these lyrics and voice touch the deepest core of our hearts and reach the inner soul.

Blessed to be born in this age and to witness you and your performances maan sahb.
